==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Reinsurance
<hw>Re`in*sur"ance</hw> <pr>(-sh?r"<it>a</it>ns)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Insurance a second time or again; renewed
insurance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A contract by which an insurer is insured wholly or
in part against the risk he has incurred in insuring somebody else. See
<er>Reassurance</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>re-insure</ent>⟦br⟧
